# [cite_start]Comprehensive ICT Infrastructure Implementation: Call Center [cite: 53]

## [cite_start]📌 Project Summary [cite: 54]
[cite_start]End-to-End infrastructure deployment for a 16-agent operations center[cite: 55]. [cite_start]The project stands out for its optimization of limited hardware resources and the integration of electrical, network, electronic security, and IP telephony layers[cite: 56].

![General Topology](./img/diagrama_ibague.png)

---

## [cite_start]🏗️ 1. Physical Infrastructure and Electrical Engineering [cite: 59]
[cite_start]The physical layer was designed and implemented, ensuring power stability and cable organization[cite: 60].

* [cite_start]**Technical Furniture:** Design and assembly of modular furniture in RH wood for workstations[cite: 61].
* [cite_start]**Electrical System:** Installation of a two-phase load center, load balancing, and dedicated UPS[cite: 62, 63, 65].

* [cite_start]**Physical Networking:** Bifurcated cabling and rack with Panduit organizers[cite: 66, 67].

---

## [cite_start]🌐 2. Network Layer and Perimeter Security [cite: 69]
[cite_start]Robust configuration to guarantee service availability and information security[cite: 70].

![Winbox Configuration](./img/image_165b58.png)

| Device | Function / Configuration |

| :--- | :--- |

| **MikroTik RB2011** | [cite_start]Router Core, Static WAN, NAT and Firewall Hardening[cite: 73]. |

**Segmentation** | [cite_start]DHCP Address Reservation for Critical Devices[cite: 74]. |

![NAT Rules](./img/NAT.png)

---

## [cite_start]📞 3. IP Telephony and Optimization (Asterisk/Issabel) [cite: 78]
[cite_start]The core of the project consisted of transforming low-resource hardware into an industrial-grade server[cite: 79].

### [cite_start]Server Optimization (Intel Core i3-2120) [cite: 80]
* [cite_start]**OS:** CentOS Minimal Installation[cite: 82].

* [cite_start]**Security:** Implementation of Fail2Ban and access via SSH Keys[cite: 84].

![Issabel Extensions](./img/extensions.png)

### [cite_start]GSM Gateway Management (Dinstar DWG2000F) [cite: 85]
* [cite_start]**1:1 Port Mapping:** Each SIP extension was linked to a physical port (SIM) of the Gateway[cite: 87].

* [cite_start]**Strategy:** Identification of line failures and consumption auditing by advisor[cite: 88].


![SIP Trunks](./img/Trunks.png)
![Outbound Routes](./img/outbound_routes.png)

---

## [cite_start]📊 4. Resource Efficiency (Actual Metrics) [cite: 90]
[cite_start]Server State After Process Optimization[cite: 91]:

| Resource | Idle State | Operational State (16 Ch) |

| :--- | :---: | :---: |

**CPU Usage** | **1%** | [cite_start]**Optimized** [cite: 94] |

**RAM Usage** | **8% (600MB)** | [cite_start]**No SWAP Usage** [cite: 95] |

![MikroTik Resources](./img/mikrotik_resources.png)

---

## [cite_start]🛠️ Tech Stack [cite: 98]
* [cite_start]**VoIP:** Asterisk, Issabel 4.0, Linphone[cite: 99].
* [cite_start]**Hardware:** MikroTik, Dinstar, Intel Core i3[cite: 100].
* [cite_start]**Security:** Hikvision, ZTE, Fail2Ban[cite: 102].





Version Español

# [cite_start]Implementación Integral de Infraestructura TIC: Call Center [cite: 53]

## [cite_start]📌 Resumen del Proyecto [cite: 54]
[cite_start]Despliegue de infraestructura "End-to-End" para un centro de operaciones de 16 asesores[cite: 55]. [cite_start]El proyecto destaca por la optimización de recursos de hardware limitado y la integración de capas eléctricas, de red, seguridad electrónica y telefonía IP[cite: 56].

![Topología General](./img/diagrama_ibague.png)

---

## [cite_start]🏗️ 1. Infraestructura Física e Ingeniería Eléctrica [cite: 59]
[cite_start]Se realizó el diseño y la ejecución de la capa física, garantizando la estabilidad energética y la organización del cableado[cite: 60].

* [cite_start]**Mobiliario Técnico:** Diseño y ensamble de muebles modulares en madera RH para estaciones de trabajo[cite: 61].
* [cite_start]**Sistema Eléctrico:** Instalación de centro de carga bifásica, balanceo de cargas y UPS dedicada[cite: 62, 63, 65].
* [cite_start]**Networking Físico:** Canalización bifurcada y Rack con organizadores Panduit[cite: 66, 67].

---

## [cite_start]🌐 2. Capa de Red y Seguridad Perimetral [cite: 69]
[cite_start]Configuración robusta para garantizar la disponibilidad del servicio y la seguridad de la información[cite: 70].

![Configuración Winbox](./img/image_165b58.png)

| Dispositivo | Función / Configuración |
| :--- | :--- |
| **MikroTik RB2011** | [cite_start]Router Core, WAN Estática, NAT y Firewall Hardening[cite: 73]. |
| **Segmentación** | [cite_start]Reserva de direcciones DHCP para dispositivos críticos[cite: 74]. |

![Reglas NAT](./img/NAT.png)

---

## [cite_start]📞 3. Telefonía IP y Optimización (Asterisk/Issabel) [cite: 78]
[cite_start]El núcleo del proyecto consistió en transformar un hardware de bajos recursos en un servidor de grado industrial[cite: 79].

### [cite_start]Optimización del Servidor (Intel Core i3-2120) [cite: 80]
* [cite_start]**OS:** Instalación de CentOS Minimal[cite: 82].
* [cite_start]**Seguridad:** Implementación de Fail2Ban y acceso mediante SSH Keys[cite: 84].

![Extensiones Issabel](./img/extensions.png)

### [cite_start]Gestión de Gateway GSM (Dinstar DWG2000F) [cite: 85]
* [cite_start]**Mapeo de Puertos 1:1:** Cada extensión SIP se vinculó a un puerto físico (SIM) del Gateway[cite: 87].
* [cite_start]**Estrategia:** Identificación de fallas de línea y auditoría de consumo por asesor[cite: 88].

![Troncales SIP](./img/Trunks.png)
![Rutas Salientes](./img/outbound_routes.png)

---

## [cite_start]📊 4. Eficiencia de Recursos (Métricas Reales) [cite: 90]
[cite_start]Estado del servidor tras la optimización de procesos[cite: 91]:

| Recurso | Estado en Reposo | Estado en Operación (16 Ch) |
| :--- | :---: | :---: |
| **Uso de CPU** | **1%** | [cite_start]**Optimizado** [cite: 94] |
| **Memoria RAM** | **8% (600MB)** | [cite_start]**Sin uso de SWAP** [cite: 95] |

![Recursos MikroTik](./img/mikrotik_resources.png)

---

## [cite_start]🛠️ Tech Stack [cite: 98]
* [cite_start]**VoIP:** Asterisk, Issabel 4.0, Linphone[cite: 99].
* [cite_start]**Hardware:** MikroTik, Dinstar, Intel Core i3[cite: 100].
* [cite_start]**Seguridad:** Hikvision, ZTE, Fail2Ban[cite: 102].
